A big ‚ÄúElevator Noob‚Äù question here‚Ä¶

Wondering if anyone knows of examples where manipulators were mounted on both sides of an elevator carriage (meaning the ‚Äúfront‚Äù and ‚Äúback‚Äù). I know there are cross beams on the ‚Äúback‚Äù of the elevator where the rigging is mounted so I don‚Äôt even know if it‚Äôs possible to do. But I‚Äôm hoping to solicit CD‚Äôs big brains to help our team find examples if they exist.

From my place of ignorance, it seems that we could also mount to the backside of the top of the first stage of the elevator and just not have it completely retract that first stage which might get around the cross beam issue‚Ä¶? We wouldn‚Äôt need full elevator height for the back side of the elevator, just 1 stage‚Äôs worth of height change potentially.

Let me know if this is not a clear question!

While I wouldn‚Äôt generally use our 2019 robot for reference, we did this by simply building a carriage that wrapped around the outside of the elevator. This meant we didn‚Äôt need to worry about pass-through clearance or designing without the top crossbrace. (I think this is the same/similar to 3641‚Äôs, but I can‚Äôt tell for sure in their images)

Was a bit janky, but with some refinement could probably work well.

All of the examples are really awesome. The ones from @alex.richards48 and @Aree_Vanier were exactly what our team members were talking about (but didn‚Äôt know how to do). Not saying we‚Äôre going to do that of course but I wanted to know that it had been done at least once before letting them run with it for a couple days prototyping.

I fully acknowledge the complexities of a choice like this. Again, appreciate all the help!!

schaefbl:

254 in 2018 or high tides elevator in 2023,

A pretty big key here is that the mechanisms themselves did not pass through the elevator here just the game object. You have a lot lower risk of something going wrong that way.

There are some robots that have passed the intake/manipulator fully through itself (1678 2019) but they scrapped that functionality mid season so Im assuming it was a pain.
